# Project Structure Guide

This is a Next.js project using the App Router pattern. Here's the key structure:

## Root Directory
- `src/` - Contains all source code
  - `app/` - Next.js App Router directory
    - `page.tsx` - Main page component
    - `layout.tsx` - Root layout component
    - `globals.css` - Global styles
- `public/` - Static assets
- `package.json` - Project dependencies and scripts
- `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript configuration
- `next.config.ts` - Next.js configuration
- `postcss.config.mjs` - PostCSS configuration
- `eslint.config.mjs` - ESLint configuration

## Key Files
- [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) - The main page component
- [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) - The root layout that wraps all pages
- [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) - Global styles and Tailwind imports
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and scripts
- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration


